            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) conducts robotic exploration of the solar system and studies Earth's systems through a portfolio of over 100 missions that define U.S. space leadership.\n* In MO-01, SMD funding supports cutting-edge research at Washington University in St. Louis, including a $9.5M award to maintain the nation's central archive for planetary geology data.\n* Every dollar invested in NASA Science returns roughly three dollars to the economy, supporting a specialized workforce in MO-01 and sustaining the domestic aerospace and innovation pipeline.\n* This $9 billion request restores stability to the agency following the workforce disruptions of FY 2026 and ensures the U.S. remains the global leader in the face of rapid Chinese space science expansion.",
