            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* The Science Mission Directorate manages NASA's planetary, Earth, astrophysics, and heliophysics programs, executing peer-reviewed priorities established by the National Academies' Decadal Surveys.\n* Local funding in MO-01 totals over $31.8M (FY23-25), supporting missions like lunar soil analysis and the development of suborbital telescopes at Washington University.\n* This programmatic request of $9 billion supports the advancement of U.S. security and economic competitiveness by solving technical challenges no private entity can replicate alone.\n* Sustained funding prevents the loss of hard-won scientific capabilities and civil servant expertise that took decades to build and are critical to the 21st-century space race.",
